page.title: 16OF INTEREST
page.content:
I am in the {SILVERBIRDS JAZZ BAND}. We wear black trousers with white and green stripes up the side, a black jacket with silver and green on the collar and a black peaked hat saying Silver birds on it. I play kazzoo. We go out every Sunday and a few Saturdays, we practise every Monday, Tuesday, Thursday, Friday. We have a single decker tour bus. {LOUISE ARGILE { *********
{STRAWBERRY HILL} was named in 1826 and is a smll mound rather than a hill. It has oak trees on it and they are quite old. Strawberry Hill could be man made and may have been a stand for hunting. There is very little information about it. Now it has a public footpath over it so people can walk and picnic there. {MATTHEW WEAVER
